The paper deals with the random generation of combinatorial structures, which is a topic that falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of different types of atoms and the targeted distribution of their occurrences suggest a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). The algorithmic approach to generating these structures also relates to data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
